docs.snippet: WIESEL--Elie. Clal mourns the loss of our co-founder Elie Wiesel, a beacon of moral conscience, a passionate defender of both the Jewish people and of universal human dignity, and a visionary social architect who inspired and created institutions ...
docs.lead_paragraph:
WIESEL--Elie.

Clal mourns the loss of our co-founder Elie Wiesel, a beacon of moral conscience, a passionate defender of both the Jewish people and of universal human dignity, and a visionary social architect who inspired and created institutions and texts which focused our attention on humankind's most important ethical questions, and helped us to answer those questions with greater efficacy and meaning. He was not only our co-founder, but our teacher and a genuine role model. May we continue to be inspired by the legacy he created in both words and deeds, and may his wife Marion, his son Elisha, his extended family, and all those who mourn the loss of this contemporary sage, find a place of comfort among those who mourn for Zion and Jerusalem. Steven J. Rotter, Chairman Rabbi Brad Hirschfield, President Rabbi Irwin Kula, President Rabbi Yitz Greenberg, Co-Founder and President Emeritus Clal--The National Jewish Center for Learning and Leadership

docs.snippet: WIESEL--Elie. The Board of Directors of Gatestone Institute mourn the loss of their esteemed Board of Advisors Member Elie Wiesel. He was the moral conscience of the world, speaking out against injustices on behalf of all of us. The world will be ...
docs.lead_paragraph:
WIESEL--Elie.

The Board of Directors of Gatestone Institute mourn the loss of their esteemed Board of Advisors Member Elie Wiesel. He was the moral conscience of the world, speaking out against injustices on behalf of all of us. The world will be a sadder place without him. Deepest condolences to dear Marion, Elisha and all the family. May his memory be an inspiration. Nina Rosenwald, President Naomi Hass-Perlman, Vice President

docs.snippet: WIESEL--Elie. The Yeshiva University family mourns the passing of Elie Wiesel, Holocaust survivor, Nobel laureate and human rights advocate. He received an honorary degree from YU in 1973 and served as an honorary trustee of Yeshiva. He said, "The...
docs.lead_paragraph:
WIESEL--Elie.

The Yeshiva University family mourns the passing of Elie Wiesel, Holocaust survivor, Nobel laureate and human rights advocate. He received an honorary degree from YU in 1973 and served as an honorary trustee of Yeshiva. He said, "The opposite of love is not hate, it's indifference." This is why he worked tirelessly to help ensure no one remained indifferent to injustice, that no one would ever forget. His life and contributions will be remembered and missed by the entire world. Heartfelt condolences are extended to his wife Marion and family. May they be comforted among all who mourn for Zion and Jerusalem. Yeshiva University Richard M. Joel, President Norman Lamm, President Emeritus

docs.snippet: WIESEL--Elie. "Tzadik Haya Bedorotav-- Righteous Man of his Generation". I mourn my friend Elie, fellow Holocaust survivor, whose memories of Auschwitz, the graveyard of our families, we shared. Anchored to Torah, he emerged from the abyss to beco...
docs.lead_paragraph:
WIESEL--Elie.

"Tzadik Haya Bedorotav-- Righteous Man of his Generation". I mourn my friend Elie, fellow Holocaust survivor, whose memories of Auschwitz, the graveyard of our families, we shared. Anchored to Torah, he emerged from the abyss to become a blessing and inspiration to the Jewish people, Israel and all of humanity. Elisabeth joins me in heartfelt condolences to Marion, his gifted Woman of Valor, his beloved son Elisha (Lynn) and grandchildren. Rabbi Arthur Schneier

docs.snippet: WIESEL--Professor Elie. Fifth Avenue Synagogue mourns the loss of its esteemed Honorary Trustee, Nobel Laureate, and global humanitarian Professor Elie Wiesel. He was a luminary, an educator, an inspiration, and above all else, a tzadik. It was a ...
docs.lead_paragraph:
WIESEL--Professor Elie.

Fifth Avenue Synagogue mourns the loss of its esteemed Honorary Trustee, Nobel Laureate, and global humanitarian Professor Elie Wiesel. He was a luminary, an educator, an inspiration, and above all else, a tzadik. It was a sincere privilege to have him daven in our pews and we will miss him greatly. His spirit continues to inspire our congregation. We extend our heartfelt condolences to Marion, Elisha, and the entire Wiesel family. Rabbi Eli Babich, Associate Rabbi Walter J. Molofsky, M.D., Chairman Jacob D. Gold, President

docs.snippet: WIESEL--Elie. With profound sadness, the staff and board of American Jewish World Service (AJWS) mourn the loss of Elie Wiesel, Holocaust survivor, Nobel laureate, tireless advocate for human rights and a founding member of our board. Wiesel helpe...
docs.lead_paragraph:
WIESEL--Elie.

With profound sadness, the staff and board of American Jewish World Service (AJWS) mourn the loss of Elie Wiesel, Holocaust survivor, Nobel laureate, tireless advocate for human rights and a founding member of our board. Wiesel helped establish AJWS thirty years ago, sharing our deep belief that the lessons of the Holocaust demand that Jews and others stand up against injustice for oppressed people everywhere. We extend our condolences to his entire family. May his memory be a call to action for human rights. Kathleen Levin, Board Chair Robert Bank, President and CEO
